Stopped in for brunch just after 11am on a Wednesday with my wife and our 18 month old son. We waited about 10 minutes for a table to open up, and then a staff person sat us. After that, no one came over to even say they'd be right with us, let alone take our drink orders. We watched people sat after us get drinks, be place orders, and still we were ignored. We certainly don't expect special treatment just because we're out with a toddler, but some acknowledgement goes a long way, especially when the kid is hungry and we're clearly song everything we can to avoid a meltdown. After waiting at least 10 minutes at the table with absolutely no interaction with a server, we put our coats on and left. Mind you, this process included suiting up our child, so there was ample time for someone to come over and at least offer an apology. Not impressed. And people wonder why local businesses are struggling. Take the criticism and make some positive changes. I'm sure we're not the only ones who have experienced this sort of thing there.
